Text.Value: I guess you've never been in love.
And now you're preparing to be thrashed for love.
And nowadays the Watch comes in a Steel variety, in case you haven't noticed. I'll take my lumps.
How about an angry patriar who broke off his daughter Henrietta's engagement with yours truly?
Why don't you get some of the other Fists to back you up against the thugs?
Who would send thugs to beat up a Flaming Fist?
No, but I expect to be, once Hurlbut Hhune's thugs catch up with me.
Hey, mate, you look pretty well geared up. Can you spare a healing potion?
You're a Flaming Fist officer. Can't you get one from your quartermaster?
Thanks for nothing, mate. At least you're polite.
If I kick up a fuss, it might blow back on Hen. She's got troubles enough - Derque Rillyn is a major arsehole.
I'd give you a healing potion if I had one, but I'm fresh out.
Have you got bugs in your head? The Fists don't mess with wealthy patriars, they've got the Watch to back them up.
Or maybe I have. Here, take this healing potion.
The Hhune family? They're rich patriars from the Upper City, aren't they?
My problem isn't exactly official business. I expect to get beaten up by some thugs hired by Hurlbut Hhune.
You don't look wounded to me.
Hurlbut Hhune must be rich if they can afford to hire thugs to attack a Flaming Fist.
So rich they piss in golden pots, or at least that's what Henrietta tells me. She's Hurlbut's daughter.
Ah, my favourite flavour, too. Thanks, mate! Don't fall for any patriars' daughters!
I'm deeply moved by your plight, Manip. Accept this healing potion, and the best of luck to you.
Leave.
We was engaged - secretly - but now it seems she's set to marry Derque Rillyn. I tried to see Hen, but papa had other ideas.
Hello again. Still got me head on me shoulders!
Leave.
You've given me a new perspective on law enforcement in Baldur's Gate. Good luck.

Synopsis: Character outside Elfsong Tavern, Manip Leythim, a Flaming Fist who has angered a patriar's father.
